OS_ReadPoint  (&32)
#Parent OS_
=>	R0 =	X coord
	R1 =	Y coord

<=	R2 =	Colour
	R3 =	Tint
	R4 =	-1 if point was off screen, 0 otherwise

This SWI returns the colour and tint of a point. If in a 16 or 32 bpp mode, this will return the 15 or 24 bit colour number in R2 and tint will be 0.
# determined experimentally by cl
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 707=>PRM-1:707>.
